Antonius Bayle<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=39733">Magelo</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 507<br> <font color=#333333>(3/6/03 10:30:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8974.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &quot;Pet Push&quot; (tm)</span><hr size=1> I've had this complaint recently... the fact is, one pet does not outpush 20+ melees.  5 pets don't, either.  This is perception, not reality, imho. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skildpade>skildpade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 240<br> <font color=#333333>(3/6/03 10:51:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8974.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &quot;Pet Push&quot; (tm)</span><hr size=1> Pets don't push more than players. However, a pet follows a mob much more closely and quickly than a player does. So where with a tank, the mob might take a step backwards and then forwards again, the pet will follow at once and lock the backward motion. Add to that crowded spaces and screwy pathing and it becomes a problem.<br>
<br>
It is however silly not to allow pets just because of push. What should be done is to instruct everyone to be spaced around the mob and possible opposite the pet(s). Also if it is possible, the pets should be set to guard at different locations so that the initial distribution of the pets aren't at one side.<br>
<br>
What could be done is having someone to look for push (could be the tank) and being in charge of calling of pets and move players.  <br>
<br>
To be blunt, a tank that can't handle push is a bad tank.<br>
